{"body": "This particular scenario, using `!` chained with `?`, seems a bit weird to my eyes:\n\n```ruby\nstate = topic.update_attributes!(params[:topic]).open?\n```\n\n(That might be just me, of course :).\n\nI just want to point that we don't usually chain ruby's `!` methods:\n\n```ruby\ntext.gsub!('foo', 'bar')\ntext.upcase!\ntext.camelize\n# rather than\ntext.gsub!('foo', 'bar').upcase!.camelize\n```\n\nJust my two cents :)\nThanks!", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7931026", "created_at": "2012-08-22T11:11:02Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7400#issuecomment-7931026", "updated_at": "2012-08-22T11:11:02Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7400, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fc05bd3543c15100b8b6"}, "id": 7931026, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issue